A massive labyrinth constructed entirely from towering stacks of manila folders, official stamps, and ribbon-bound documents, viewed from above in isometric perspective. Tiny figures in business attire wander the maze's corridors, some carrying oversized rubber stamps like shields, others pushing carts overflowing with paperwork. The walls of the labyrinth cast long shadows, and at the center sits an ornate golden trophy on a pedestal, unreachable due to dead ends. The color palette features muted bureaucratic beiges, dusty blues, and faded greens with occasional pops of red wax seals. Rendered in a vintage 1950s government poster illustration style with visible halftone dots and slightly faded ink quality, evoking mid-century administrative aesthetics.
